{"aid": "http://arxiv.org/abs/2504.05063v1", "title": "Observation of the doubly-charmed-baryon decay ${\it
  Ξ}_{cc}^{++}\to{\it Ξ}_{c}^{0}π^{+}π^{+}$", "summary": "A search for the doubly-charmed-baryon decay ${\it \Xi}_{cc}^{++}\to{\it
\Xi}_{c}^{0}(\to p K^{-}K^{-}\pi^{+})\pi^{+}\pi^{+}$ is performed using
proton-proton collision data collected by the LHCb experiment at a
centre-of-mass energy of 13 $\text{TeV}$ and corresponding to an integrated
luminosity of 5.4 $\text{fb}^{-1}$. A significant structure consistent with the
${\it \Xi}_{cc}^{++}$ baryon is observed in the ${\it \Xi}_{c}^{0} \pi^{+}
\pi^{+}$ invariant-mass spectrum. Using the ${\it \Xi}_{cc}^{++}\to{\it
\Lambda}_{c}^{+}(\to pK^{-}\pi^{+})K^{-}\pi^{+}\pi^{+}$ decay as the
normalisation channel, the branching fraction ratio \begin{equation*}
  \frac{{\cal B}({\it \Xi}_{cc}^{++} \to {\it
\Xi}_{c}^{0}\pi^{+}\pi^{+})\times{\cal B}({\it \Xi}_{c}^{0}\to
pK^{-}K^{-}\pi^{+})} {{\cal B}({\it \Xi}_{cc}^{++}\to{\it \Lambda}_{c}^{+}
K^{-}\pi^{+}\pi^{+})\times{\cal B}({\it \Lambda}_{c}^{+}\to pK^{-}\pi^{+})}
\end{equation*} is measured to be $0.105\pm 0.014\text{\,(stat)} \pm
0.007\text{\,(syst)}$.", "main_category": "hep-ex", "categories": "hep-ex", "published": "2025-04-07T13:34:01Z"}
